article.description: Loyola (Md) beats Catholic in second half, 87-75
article.headline: Loyola (Md) beats Catholic in second half, 87-75
article.linkText: Loyola (Md) beats Catholic in second half, 87-75
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Dylon Cormier scored 23 points and Franz Rassman added 10 of his 14 in the second half as Loyola (Md.) pulled away from Division III Catholic in the final 20 minutes for an 87-75 win Wednesday night. The Greyhounds (5-2) shot 53 percent (35-66) and had five players score in double figures. Jarred Jones and Tyler Hubbard came off the bench to score 13 and 11 points, respectively and Jordan Latham added another 10. Bryson Fonville had 19 points and dished off 13 assists to lead the Cardinals (3-2). Steve Limberiou scored 11 points and Kyle Phanord and Corey Stanford each contributed 10 points. Catholic hit three of four free throws at the end of the first half to send the teams into intermission tied, 39-39. Rassman had a pair of layups in the first four minutes of the second half to help Loyola build a 51-43 lead.
